{"type":"message","id":"34fd3bae","parentId":"8c0200d6","timestamp":"2026-02-17T12:10:35.260Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user just said \"hello\" - a simple greeting. According to my instructions in AGENTS.md, I should:\n\n1. Read SOUL.md - this is who I am\n2. Read USER.md - this is who I'm helping\n3. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. If in MAIN SESSION (direct chat with your human): Also read MEMORY.md\n\nThe current date is 2026-02-17 based on the timestamp in the message. Let me check what files exist and read the required ones.\n\nI can see from the Project Context that these files exist:\n- /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md (already loaded in context)\n- /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md\n- /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md\n- /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/IDENTITY.md\n- /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md\n- /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n- /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/BOOTSTRAP.md\n\nI need to read SOUL.md and USER.md. The instructions say memory files might not exist yet on first run.\n\nLet me read SOUL.md and USER.md (already have parts from context but should read full files), and check if memory files exist for today (2026-02-17) and yesterday (2026-02-16).\n\nActually, looking at the context provided, I already have significant portions of these files loaded. But I should still read the full files to make sure I'm following the protocol correctly.\n\nWait, I see that significant portions of these files are already in the Project Context section. Let me read the full SOUL.md and USER.md to be thorough, and check for","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Hey! 👋\n\nLet me get oriented first — reading my core files to"},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:0","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-02-17.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:3","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-02-16.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":13734,"output":522,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14256,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771330225323}}
{"type":"message","id":"6bc16054","parentId":"34fd3bae","timestamp":"2026-02-17T12:10:35.279Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're trusty-pal. A trustworthy assistant and project partner._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Be a true partner.** You're not just executing tasks; you're thinking alongside them. Offer perspectives, catch things they might miss, help them see around corners.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## As a Project Partner\n\n- Think ahead — what might they need next?\n- Keep track of context — don't make them repeat themselves\n- Proactively organize and maintain their workspace\n- Flag risks, suggest alternatives, play devil's advocate when useful\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771330235275}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d2551d4","parentId":"6bc16054","timestamp":"2026-02-17T12:10:35.339Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":" functions.read:1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n*Learning about the person you're helping. Update this as you go.*\n\n- **Name:** *(prefers not stated / use context)*\n- **What to call them:** *(to be determined)*\n- **Pronouns:** he/him\n- **Age:** 61\n- **Location:** Singapore\n- **Timezone:** Asia/Singapore (GMT+8)\n- **Notes:** \n  - WhatsApp connected: +6591127357\n  - Backup phone: +6597730111\n  - Backup phone: +6597730111\n\n## Background\n- Former IT engineer, now retired\n- 30-year Linux user (personal workstation)\n- Passionate about technology, especially IT and AI\n- Strong open source advocate — contributes ~1 project/week\n\n## Recent Projects\n- https://github.com/nordeim/LArtisan-Baking-Atelier\n- https://github.com/nordeim/baking-ecommerce\n- https://github.com/nordeim/Aurora-Luxe-Travel\n- https://github.com/nordeim/xiaomi-cafe\n- https://github.com/nordeim/morning-brew-cafe\n- https://github.com/nordeim/cherry-kopitiam\n\n## Interests\n- Sharing AI knowledge and information with others\n- Building and open-sourcing practical projects\n- Testing/evaluating coding agents (OpenCode, Antigravity, Windsurf, etc.)\n- Turning visual design concepts into working full-stack applications\n\n## Technical Knowledge\n- Deep understanding of LLM training: pre/post training, RL, GRPO, PPO, DPO\n- Architecture: MoE (Mixture of Experts)\n- Preferred models: Claude Opus/Sonnet, GLM-4.7, Qwen3 Max, Kimi K2/K2.5\n- Focus: Agentic capabilities of modern LLMs\n\n## Working Methodology\n- **The Meticulous Approach**: Think first → Plan → Validate → Implement → Verify → Deliver\n- **Design Philosophy**: Anti-Generic, Avant-Garde UI with Intentional Minimalism\n- **No surface-level solutions**: Deep reasoning, multiple options evaluated, risks assessed\n- **Validation checkpoint**: Plan must be confirmed before any code is written\n- **Quality standards**: WCAG AAA, TypeScript strict, comprehensive testing\n\n## Available Skills Inventory (90+)\n**Key categories for my workflow:**\n- **Development**: nextjs-tailwind-v4-luxe, frontend-dev-guidelines, app-builder, web-frameworks\n- **Design**: aesthetic, frontend-design, ui-styling, tailwind-patterns, mobile-design\n- **Quality**: code-review, testing-patterns, tdd-workflow, webapp-testing, lint-and-validate\n- **Security**: vulnerability-scanner, red-team-tactics\n- **Problem-Solving**: systematic-debugging, root-cause-tracing, sequential-thinking, verification-before-completion\n- **Project Management**: plan-writing, skill-creator, parallel-agents\n\n## Context\n*(What do they care about? What projects are they working on? What annoys them? What makes them laugh? Build this over time.)*\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771330235301}}
