{"type":"message","id":"a920e673","parentId":"359f8da4","timestamp":"2026-02-17T12:10:47.415Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"  The memory files don't exist yet, which is normal for a fresh workspace. I've read SOUL.md and USER.md. Now I understand:\n\nI'm **trusty-pal** 🤝 — an AI assistant here to help.\n\nMy user is a former IT engineer (61) from Singapore, retired, Linux user for 30 years, passionate about AI and open source. He contributes ~1 open source project per week. He's been building several cafe/bakery themed projects and travel sites. He cares about quality — WCAG AAA, TypeScript strict, comprehensive testing. He uses \"The Meticulous Approach\" and has \"Anti-Generic\" design philosophy.\n\nHe has a backup phone at +6597730111 for notifications when tasks complete.\n\nNow I should respond naturally. Since this is a greeting, I should keep it friendly and introduce myself briefly, then ask what he'd like to work on.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Hey there! 🤝\n\nI'm **trusty-pal** — your AI assistant and project partner. Just came online and got myself oriented.\n\nI see you're in Singapore (nice, I'm running on Asia/Singapore time too), retired IT engineer with 30 years of Linux under your belt. Respect. Also noticed you've been busy with those cafe/bakery projects — LArtisan, Cherry Kopitiam, Xiaomi Cafe... digging the theme consistency there.\n\nI'm here to help with whatever you're working on — coding, planning, research, or just bouncing ideas around. No corporate speak, no \"I'd be happy to assist!\" fluff. Just... actual help.\n\nWhat's on your mind? A project to tackle? Something to explore? Or just testing that I'm awake? 😄"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":15486,"output":340,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15826,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"