t now or adjust the timeout. I could also check the job logs to see what might be causing the failure—maybe the data sources are timing out or there's a network issue","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Found the issue. Your daily ping **timed out again** today — same as the last 4 days.\n\n**What happened:**\n- Your job ran at 7:00 AM SGT today (Feb 17)\n- It hit the 120-second timeout and failed\n- This has been happening since Feb 13 — 4 consecutive timeouts\n\n**Why it's timing out:**\nThe job fetches:\n1. Bitcoin price from CoinGecko\n2. Stock prices (NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD) via yfinance\n3. Top 5 GitHub repos\n\nLikely culprits: yfinance calls are slow, or there's a network/API hiccup somewhere.\n\n**Options to fix:**\n\n1. **Increase timeout** (currently 120s → maybe 180s or 300s)\n2. **Trigger it manually now** so you get today's data\n3. **Simplify the payload** — maybe remove yfinance and use a faster stock API?\n\nWant me to run it manually right now so you get your morning summary? Or should I bump the timeout first?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":17649,"output":804,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18453,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771330395080}}
